<description>After making his senior debut for Wycombe Wanderers at the end of the 1999-2000 campaign, Roger found it difficult to break into the first-team squad in 2000-01 and his only opportunity came from the subs' bench at Reading in March when he gave an assured performance.
A talented central defender, Roger's contract at Wycombe Wanderers was extended to June 2007 in December 2004.
His contract at Cardiff City was extended to June 2011 in July 2008.
Roger joined Birmingham City in July 2009 with a three-year contract.</description>

